''Oddfellows'' was released on January 29, 2013 through [[Ipecac Recordings]],<ref name="spin">{{cite web |url=http://www.spin.com/articles/tomahawk-first-lp-in-six-years-stone-letter |title=Hear the Gnashing First Taste of Tomahawk's First LP in Six Years |date=October 4, 2012 |first=Christopher R. |last=Weingarten |work=[[Spin (magazine)|Spin]] |accessdate=October 4, 2012}}</ref> the label owned by Patton.<ref name="avc"/> The album had been completed for several months by this point, but its release date was moved back as the band's members did not have time to promote an earlier release.<ref name="cons int"/> To support the album's release, the band played at the [[Voodoo Experience]] music festival in [[New Orleans]], [[Louisiana]] in October 2012;<ref name="consequence">{{cite web |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/06/mike-pattons-tomahawk-announces-new-album-oddfellows/ |title=Mike Patton<U+2019>s Tomahawk announces new album: Oddfellows |work=[[Consequence of Sound]] |first=Alex |last=Young |date=June 28, 2012 |accessdate=October 4, 2012}}</ref> and the [[Austin, Texas]] [[Fun Fun Fun Fest]],<ref name="stone"/> along with several tour dates in the United States in October and November.<ref name="spin"/>

The band initially announced the release of "Waratorium" as a [[Seven-inch|seven-inch record]] as part of [[Record Store Day]]'s "Black Friday" event on November 23, 2012;<ref name="con2">{{cite web |url=http://consequenceofsound.net/2012/10/new-music-tomahawk-stone-letter/ |title=New Music: Tomahawk <U+2013> "Stone Letter" |work=[[Consequence of Sound]] |first=Michael |last=Roffman |date=October 4, 2012 |accessdate=November 21, 2012}}</ref> eventually releasing "Stone Letter" instead. The single featured illustrations by Brunetti, and was released as a digital download on December 4, 2012. Its accompanying music video was directed by Vincent Forcier, using concert footage from Tomahawk's 2012 concerts.<ref name="pitchfork stone letter">{{cite web |url=http://pitchfork.com/news/48778-watch-the-video-for-the-mike-patton-lead-group-tomahawks-first-song-in-six-years-stone-letter/ |title=Watch the Video for the Mike Patton-Lead Group Tomahawk's First Song in Six Years, "Stone Letter" |first=Carrie |last=Battan |date=November 30, 2012 |work=[[Pitchfork Media]] |accessdate=December 4, 2012}}</ref>

''Oddfellows'' debuted at number sixteen on the [[UK Rock Chart]] album countdown on February 9, 2013, spending one week in the chart.<ref name="ukchart">{{cite web |url=http://www.officialcharts.com/archive-chart/_/11/2013-02-09/ |title=2013-02-09 Top 40 Rock & Metal Albums Archive |publisher=[[The Official Charts Company]] |accessdate=May 5, 2013}}</ref> In the United States, ''Oddfellows'' recorded positions in several of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' magazine's charts<U+2014>reaching a peak position of 69 on the [[Billboard 200|''Billboard'' 200]], 12 on the [[Alternative Albums]] listings, second place on the [[Hard Rock Albums]] chart, and ninth on the [[Independent Albums]] chart.<ref name="billboard">{{cite web |url={{BillboardURLbyName|artist=tomahawk|chart=all}} |title=Tomahawk <U+2013> Chart History |work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]] |publisher=[[Prometheus Global Media]] |accessdate=May 5, 2013}} Note: Use the drop-down selection to toggle individual charts.</ref> ''Oddfellows'' also reached chart positions in Australia, Belgium and Finland. The album reached number 37 on the [[ARIA Charts]],<ref name="aust">{{cite web |url=http://australian-charts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Tomahawk&titel=OddfellowS&cat=a |title=australian-charts.com&nbsp;<U+2013> Tomahawk&nbsp;<U+2013> Oddfellows |work=australian-charts.com |accessdate=May 5, 2013}}</ref> 137 in the [[Ultratop]] countdown,<ref name="belg">{{cite web |url=http://www.ultratop.be/nl/showitem.asp?interpret=Tomahawk&titel=OddfellowS&cat=a |title=ultratop.be&nbsp;<U+2013> Tomahawk&nbsp;<U+2013> Oddfellows |work=ultratop.be |accessdate=May 5, 2013}}</ref> and 26 in [[The Official Finnish Charts]].<ref name="fin">{{cite web |url=http://finnishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Tomahawk&titel=OddfellowS&cat=a |title=finnishcharts.com&nbsp;<U+2013> Tomahawk&nbsp;<U+2013> Oddfellows |work=finnishcharts.com |accessdate=May 5, 2013}}</ref>

==Reception==

